RandomX
------------------------------------------
RandomX is a proof-of-work (PoW) algorithm that is optimized for
general-purpose CPUs. RandomX uses random code execution (hence the name)
together with several memory-hard techniques to minimize the efficiency
advantage of specialized hardware.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  librandomx-devel-1.1.8-1bl1
  librandomx0-1.1.8-1bl1
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tevador/RandomX

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tevador/RandomX/archive/v1.1.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack RandomX-1.1.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./RandomX-1.1.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/RandomX-1.1.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/RandomX-1.1.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librandomx0-1.1.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librandomx-devel-1.1.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(RandomX)
  /usr/bin/randomx-benchmark.exe
  /usr/bin/randomx-codegen.exe
  /usr/bin/randomx-tests.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/RandomX.README
  /usr/share/doc/RandomX/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/RandomX/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/RandomX/configuration.md
  /usr/share/doc/RandomX/design.md
  /usr/share/doc/RandomX/specs.md

(librandomx0)
  /usr/bin/cygrandomx-0.dll

(librandomx-devel)
  /usr/include/randomx.h
  /usr/lib/librandomx.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/RandomX.pc

